name: phospholipid-translocating ATPase
classes: Acting on acid anhydrides to catalyse transmembrane movement of substances
reaction: ATP + H2O + phospholipid[side 1] = ADP + phosphate + phospholipid[side 2] [RN:R00086]
comment: A P-type ATPase that undergoes covalent phosphorylation during the transport cycle. The enzyme moves phospholipids such as phosphatidylcholine, phosphatidylserine, and phosphatidylethanolamine from one membrane face to the other ('flippase').
